  "prompt": "What are some of the most common examples of an imperative sentence?",
  "response": "An imperative sentence gives a command, makes a request, or offers instructions. Here are some common examples:\n\n1. **Close the door.**\n2. **Please sit down.**\n3. **Turn off the lights.**\n4. **Wash your hands.**\n5. **Help me with this.**\n6. **Don't touch that.**\n7. **Listen carefully.**\n8. **Take a seat.**\n9. **Finish your homework.**\n10. **Call me later.**\n\nThese sentences often begin with a verb and can be firm or polite based on the context and the inclusion of words like \"please.\"",
